DSET Standartization AI 

 

Make sure the solution architecture of the project is clear and documented 

Make sure you have a Jira ticket on the project 

Verify Your code is connected\Saved to the Azure Dev Ops Repository 

https://dev.azure.com/ 

 

Make sure that you work with the same repo name on Dev/Test & Prod environments. 
 
For example: MMIT on Dev, MMIT_CDW on Prod. Please make sure that same repo is used across the environment. 

 

code file have clear naming convention.  

Ex. PROJECT NAME – DATA Ingestion\Model\Configuration 

Each code file has a README section at the beginning. 

Ex.  

######################## 

## Project name : 

## Business owner , Team : 

## Notebook Author , Team: 

##Date: 

##Puprose of Notebook: 

######################## 

If there are connection between code files , this should be mentioned in the file's top readme section 

Comment on each Function , each section. As much comments as possible 

If there are more than two envs: dev , prod . you must have the env as parameter for the ci\cd pipeline. 
 
Make sure that you are not hardcoding anything which changes based on the environments,  

Variables with clear naming convention (no x,y,z,i) 

Function names, Data Frames names with clear naming convention (no df , func) 

There should be a data validation part. Make sure no drifting in column names, column values. 

All code sections will be unified in the code in one place e.g. imports of packages in one section . (imports , functions , declarations , settings variables ) 

Each section will be separated from the other section in a clear manner with a comment statement . 

Example:  ###############  IMPORT PACKAGES  ############### 

 

Avoid hardcoding of secrets or passwords in the code files and access them through key vault. 

print statements within the code should be send to a log or a file  

Make sure that the next environments are prepared in the same configuration 

Use managed identity or Service Principle to connect to other systems if needed.  

The code will be reviewed by external person who has coding skills and is not related to the development of the project. 

When creating a code , write it in the most general reusable way possible , for other project's usage 

All Promotions between environments will be done via ci\cd automation. 

Part of the flow of the ci\cd , is an approval step, by people who are external to the promoted project. 

All promotions will be documented and deployed by certified people  

All packages in the code must be downloaded from Teva secured package repository. 

Logging as much as possible 

Send events to EventHub to monitor the execution of the notebook and identify the failure of the code in the code files. 

Alerts in case there is a failure in the web application 

Cost for each application and model is clear 

Authentication in the webapp will be through ENTRAID 

All permissions in the webapp will be conducted with AD Groups. 

All entities in the AD Groups will be requested through IDM 

Every component that has a description – must add the description of the project. 

Promotions should be at least two weeks notice before.  

 

 

 

 

 
